    1785 DSAP Computes an inertial or pseudo-load matrix Main Index Remarks: 1.The number of rows PX is equal to the number of rows in the input matrices. The number of columns in PX is also equal to the number of columns in the input matrices unless DSPT1 is specified, in which case the number of columns is equal to the number of columns in the input matrices times the design variables defined in DSPT1. 2.If the number of columns in the MUX, BUX, and KUX is less than the number of frequencies in OL then PX will be truncated accordingly. 3.Any of the inputs may be purged except for OL. If DSPT1 is specified then APP can only be equal to ‘FREQ’ and the summation is repeated for each design variable and the result is called pseudo- loads. Also, the result is the negative of the equation above. 4.The input matrices can have any number of rows. For example, the number of rows could relate to a degree-of-freedom set.‘CEIG’ Complex eigenvalue ‘REIG’ Normal modes
